@page "/how-enigma-works"

<SeoHead Title="Enigma Operations Guide | Expedition Flow Reference"
         Description="Understand expedition flow, puzzle interaction, rewards, sector ownership, and how Enigma research systems connect to daily play."
         OpenGraphType="article"
         SchemaType="Article"
         Keywords="Enigma operations guide, anomaly expeditions, E-Unit controls, sector run rules" />

<div class="content seo-page-shell">
    <section class="panel seo-page-hero">
        <div class="panel-heading">
            <div>
                <span class="profile-kicker">Operations Guide</span>
                <h1>How Explorer Operations Work</h1>
            </div>
            <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/home">Back</a>
        </div>
        <p>Each expedition starts with a generated or saved sector. From there, you move room to room, solve puzzle locks, collect rewards, and reach the finish room before the expedition is abandoned or completed.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Expedition Flow</h2>
        <h3>Initialize a Sector</h3>
        <p>Generate a new sector or load a mapped sector. Before entry, choose available field tools and launch the expedition.</p>
        <h3>Resolve Rooms</h3>
        <p>Rooms use direct interactions and console overlays. Some puzzles resolve in-room, while others open through the console with the <code>E</code> key.</p>
        <h3>Complete or Lose</h3>
        <p>Expeditions are permanent. Leaving a live sector counts as a loss. Successful completion awards MN, progression, and potential sector outcomes.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Rewards and Progress</h2>
        <h3>MN Credits</h3>
        <p>Room rewards, completions, daily systems, and economy activity all contribute to your MN balance.</p>
        <h3>Mapped Sectors</h3>
        <p>Discoveries can become persistent sectors with market value, owner history, ratings, and ranking relevance.</p>
        <h3>Analysis and Council Voting</h3>
        <p>Owned sectors can be assigned to analysis for daily MN. Analyzed sector count also contributes to council vote weighting.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Live Systems</h2>
        <h3>Real-Time Updates</h3>
        <p>Contact requests, invites, explorer status, and key research and voting updates are surfaced through in-app notifications.</p>
        <h3>Research Dashboard</h3>
        <p>The research tab tracks circulating MN, sector distribution, listings, analysis status, and activity trends.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Quick Questions</h2>
        <h3>What happens if I leave a sector?</h3>
        <p>Leaving a live expedition ends it permanently and records it as lost.</p>
        <h3>Do all puzzles use the console?</h3>
        <p>No. Some puzzles are solved directly in the room with movement and interaction, while others use the console overlay.</p>
        <h3>Can I replay or trade mapped sectors?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Mapped sectors can be replayed, rated, listed, sold, or assigned to analysis if you own them.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="panel seo-page-section">
        <h2>Continue Orientation</h2>
        <div class="seo-link-grid">
            <a class="seo-link-card" href="/about">
                <strong>Program Brief</strong>
                <span>How Enigma Corporation and A.R.D connect explorers, sectors, and governance.</span>
            </a>
            <a class="seo-link-card" href="/enigma-game-mechanics">
                <strong>System Mechanics</strong>
                <span>Room logic, puzzle mechanics, sector lifecycle, and progression rules.</span>
            </a>
            <a class="seo-link-card" href="/enigma-multiplayer">
                <strong>Co-op Operations</strong>
                <span>Shared command sessions, live invites, synchronized movement, and co-op completion.</span>
            </a>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>
